The Kaduna State Police Command has banned the activities of volunteer security outfits known as Yan Sa Kai/Yan Bula throughout the state. The Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Yakubu Sabo, disclosed this in a statement yesterday. He stated: “Thus, on no account should any person or group of persons parade themselves as Yan Sa Kai/ Yan Bula and perform any form of voluntary security assignment within the Command.” He said the command would deal decisively with any person or group of persons violating the order using the apparatus of the law. Police ban activities of volunteer security outfits in Kaduna Ba Beli: A notorious killer gang pushing Bauchi towards the cliff Birnin Gwari attack: Police deploy 3 MOPOL Units Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin